headline: CVS Q1 Earnings Call: Guidance Raised Amid Segment Shifts and Pharmacy Innovation
summary: Diversified healthcare company CVS Health (NYSE:CVS) announced better-than-expected revenue in Q1 CY2025, with sales up 7% year on year to $94.59 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.25 per share was 34.6% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
